<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-44-1030 </DOCNO><TEXT>The recent joint venture deal signed between Texaco and Saudi Arabia hasthrown the spotlight back on to a trend, apparent in recent years, ofoil-producing nations investing in the refining and marketing industriesof Western oil-consuming nations. Two producers - Kuwait and Venezuela- have been piecing together quite a network of downstream assets inrecent years, others have been doing a lot of talking without conclusion.Quality downstream assets are not so readily available and there is evidenceto suggest that the trend is unlikely to continue unless the producersare willing to compromise and exchange assets: notably shares in oilreserves.</TEXT></DOC>